commit_message:
Followup for multiple member_of qparams support

* Function documentation of member_of param is fixed in multiple places
* Defaulting member_of to None instead of empty string to use a value
  that the caller documented to expect
* Fixing placement db test case that still used a single UUID list as
  member_of

Change-Id: I9b7184f8f8b1e621df61b5652956707345be2ab0

commit_message:
Sanitize the config drive UUID

When cloud-init processes an instance to determine
if it is first boot or not, it compares the config
drive UUID with the VM UUID.  This change makes those
values the same now for a given VM / config drive pair.

Change-Id: I128a0bc886b020d67241c67a874cf8d06e791b57

commit_message:
Make validation failure on node deploy a 4XX code

Missing information and other validation issues with instance_info is a
user error and should be a 4XX code HTTP response, currently Ironic
responds with a 5XX code indicating something has gone wrong with the
service.

Change-Id: If76e2aba97e0ed9fa63ad3c411ed92969164d3dc
Story: #2001983
Task: #19600

I then switched to just toggling it off/on."}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-04-26 22:11:12.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 11805, 'date': '2018-05-01 20:38:44.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

I think this patch generally looks good. I'm just having a hard time understanding if the opinionated defaults are good. Maybe the config.yaml should have a bit more detail on limitations, in other words, a general interpretation of the config values in place."}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-01 21:29:25.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-01 21:30:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Thanks for the review Corey! I re-worded the description in config.yaml. Let me know if this still needs tweaking or not.'}, {'account_id': 11805, 'date': '2018-05-02 14:03:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

(1 comment)

Hey Shane, thanks and a couple more comments.'}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-02 15:07:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Corey,
Apologies, appears I got my wires crossed a bit. max_segment_size isn't a valid setting. Rather it's min_segment_size. This would allow the user to upload segments >= 1M.
Using this default 1M value, would allow uploading objects up to 1TB, after enabling slo. 

If the client specifies a larger segment size (<=max_file_size per https://docs.openstack.org/newton/config-reference/object-storage/features.html#constraints), this would greatly increase the maximum object size for upload when using slo.

The max_manifest_size is specified in bytes, so this would become 512M I believe. This value seems sufficient considering the maximum segments being allowed.

Regarding the timeout. I need to confirm this, but I believe the timeout value is per-segment. If this is the case, should we still consider raising this timeout?"}, {'account_id': 11805, 'date': '2018-05-02 17:09:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Ok so I think the min object size is 1TB and the max object size is actually 5 petabytes if my calculations are correct. Is that what you were expecting?

min = 1TB = 1MB(min_segment_size) * 1000000(max_manifest_segments)
max = 5PB = 5GB(max_file_size) * 1000000(max_manifest_segments)
 
Yes you're right, max_manifest_size is 512MB. That seems reasonable.

As for timeout, I'm not sure. That would have to be tested with some really large values I think."}, {'account_id': 11805, 'date': '2018-05-02 17:10:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

I meant timeout would have to be tested with really large objects.'}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-02 18:01:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Yes, that would be the theoretical largest object you could store. One particular use case is a backup service that stores VM images in swift which uses 32MB segments. With the default max_manifest_segments of 1000, we're capped at 32GB.

With this patch, our max is of course 32TB. Which certainly does seem high. However, it's hard to know the exact use case of the user.

The question becomes, in our attempt at setting opinionated defaults to accommodate a variety of use cases, do we cap the max object size (via max_manifest_segments), and if so, where."}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-02 19:31:01.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-02 19:34:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-02 19:39:30.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 11805, 'date': '2018-05-03 13:14:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6:

(3 comments)

Looks good. I have some minor suggestions for the config.yaml description, then I'm ready to approve."}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-04 13:56:52.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 7.'}, {'account_id': 11805, 'date': '2018-05-04 14:17:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review+1

LGTM, thanks!'}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-04 14:24:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

Thanks Corey. One question, I know it's non-voting, but are there compatibility problems with python 3+ and the test I'm using in the templates?"}, {'account_id': 11805, 'date': '2018-05-04 14:32:22.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

Hmm not sure but I do see the errors in http://logs.openstack.org/46/564546/7/check/openstack-tox-py35/8871a6b/job-output.txt.gz where the jinja2 template is not understanding the variable name. Let's check with others in #openstack-charms."}, {'account_id': 935, 'date': '2018-05-09 08:16:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review+1

charm-recheck-full'}, {'account_id': 935, 'date': '2018-05-09 13:35:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 24297, 'date': '2018-05-09 20:41:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Cherry Picked

This patchset was cherry picked to branch stable/18.02 as commit e5c030330730b14ff7ba9e2fea32ce4a16bc2e3f'}]

commit_message:
Add support for Static Large Objects

Adds the necessary filter to the swift-proxy config
to support Static Large Objects (SLO).

A new config value 'static-large-object-segments' toggles
SLO support and allows the user to control the maximum object
size when set to a value >0.

Change-Id: I42a88292775badb9fd70e5b99558d084ddcdc29f
Closes-Bug: 1753811

commit_message:
MariaDB: Fronting proxy

This PS adds a fronting tcp proxy with A/P to the backends. This
Change removes the issue of DB deadlocks when using multi-master
galera databases.

Change-Id: I3294d4e9d9258a98692292fa5da16505bfa9ecd6

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for feature/deep-review

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: If428785c7b0276703e9a62f14ab1f35224bb9068

commit_message:
Clean up floating ip tests

There are timeout issues as well as sometimes something goes wrong in
the shade floating ip tests. Update the tests to try to make them more
stable.

This also fixes a bug in find_available_ip that was causing ips with
port_ids to be returned that was accidentally working in the functional
tests as a race condition.

While working on this, pycodestyle made a release and broke us. Add pep8
changes to allow landing this patch. Fix two of them, ignore two of them.

Change-Id: I128e85048b91f0508798d6c0c2a7e3aacb1c92c1

[{'created': '2018-05-04 17:43:22.000000000', 'message': "Update ceph-osd-check-udev to correct an awk condition

The awk statement will print 1 if the ceph release it < 0.94.
Otherwise, it will print nothing. When it does not print anything,
no value is set to DISABLE_UDEV. This results in the test failing.

++ ceph --version
++ awk 'match($3, /[0-9]+\.[0-9]+/) {if (substr($3, RSTART, RLENGTH) <= 0.94) {print 1}}'
+ DISABLE_UDEV=
+ test -f /usr/lib/udev/rules.d/95-ceph-osd.rules
+ test -eq 1
sh: line 3: test: -eq: unary operator expected

This patch adds a 'else { print 0 }' if the substr does not return true.

++ ceph --version
++ awk 'match($3, /[0-9]+\.[0-9]+/) {if (substr($3, RSTART, RLENGTH) <= 0.94) {print 1} else { print 0 } }'
+ DISABLE_UDEV=0
+ test -f /usr/lib/udev/rules.d/95-ceph-osd.rules
+ test 0 -eq 1

Change-Id: I4d2da48717c57b0d8d853d9e2a711ca02b18c6e1

Change-Id: I4d2da48717c57b0d8d853d9e2a711ca02b18c6e1

commit_message:
Update ceph-osd-check-udev to correct an awk condition

The awk statement will print 1 if the ceph release it < 0.94.
Otherwise, it will print nothing. When it does not print anything,
no value is set to DISABLE_UDEV. This results in the test failing.

++ ceph --version
++ awk 'match($3, /[0-9]+\.[0-9]+/) {if (substr($3, RSTART, RLENGTH) <= 0.94) {print 1}}'
+ DISABLE_UDEV=
+ test -f /usr/lib/udev/rules.d/95-ceph-osd.rules
+ test -eq 1
sh: line 3: test: -eq: unary operator expected

This patch adds a 'else { print 0 }' if the substr does not return true.

++ ceph --version
++ awk 'match($3, /[0-9]+\.[0-9]+/) {if (substr($3, RSTART, RLENGTH) <= 0.94) {print 1} else { print 0 } }'
+ DISABLE_UDEV=0
+ test -f /usr/lib/udev/rules.d/95-ceph-osd.rules
+ test 0 -eq 1

Replace Chinese punctuation with English punctuation

Curly quotes(Chinese punctuation) usually input from Chinese input method.

commit_message:
Remove unused methods in nova/compute/utils.py

The following methods in nova/compute/utils.py
have not been used since
I9269ffa2b80e48db96c622d0dc0817738854f602.

* reverse_upsize_quota_delta
* downsize_quota_delta

the 'upsize_quota_delta' method in the file.

commit_message:
Delay collectd start

We need to make collectd container start in the same step as Gnocchi,
so that we avoid occasional connection problems with collectd deployed
without working Keystone and Gnocchi.

Change-Id: Ifce5d3a7395d9ddf99e2d9097f71a222e8c64487

commit_message:
PXE Filter dnsmasq: Purge cleared files

If configuration option purge_dhcp_hostsdir is set
to purge the dhcp_hostdir any files that has been
cleared will be purged on periodic update.

Cleared files are empty remains from ports not
kept in ironic anymore.

Story: 2001979
Task: 19590
Change-Id: If5507562622c8694c90759f4c1ad687ca8acb994

[{'created': '2018-05-09 01:13:22.000000000', 'message': 'Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various

- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default

commit_message:
Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html

Also fixes the lower-constraints file to allow the CI to pass.

Change-Id: I7d61303c145784c86d95ccc5cd58f4ced376a713

commit_message:
Vagrantfile: Increase VM memory requirements to 6GB

Running the os_tempest role on Vagrant VMs often leads to the following
error:

==> ubuntu1604: TASK [galera_client : Add keys (primary keyserver)] ****************************
==> ubuntu1604: ERROR! Unexpected Exception, this is probably a bug: [Errno 12] Cannot allocate memory
==> ubuntu1604: to see the full traceback, use -vvv
==> ubuntu1604: ERROR: InvocationError for command '/bin/bash -c /vagrant/tests/common/test-ansible-functional.sh' (exited with code 250)

As such lets increase the memory requirements to 6GB. Moreover, we
switch to the Bento boxes which come with 65GB of diskspace and they are
all built from a central place. Hopefully, this will bring some
uniformity across the Vagrant VMs. This also removes the
openSUSE Leap 42.2 configuration since it's reached EOL.

Change-Id: Iba357117d19670f245e999ffdeb5c954d76443e8

Add queue_name parameter to ffwd_converge

FFU: ceph upgrade fails and exits with 'queue_name'. It looks that
the upgrade completed ok but in the end it exits with the
'queue_name'. This is caused by missing parameter.

commit_message:
Make manila-ui python3 compatible

In order to make manila-ui python3 compatible,
this patch set:
- replace dict.iteritems() with six.iteritems(dict)
- replace print msg with print(msg)
- replace dict.viewkeys() with error.keys()
- python 3 getting the keys() of a dict returns
  a dict_keys object instead of a list and hence
  sort() fails
- in python 2.x calling keys makes a copy of the key
  that you can iterate over while modifying the dict.
  This doesn't work in python 3.x because keys
  returns an iterator instead of a list.
  Another way is to use list to force a copy of the keys
  to be made.
- use getattr instead of relying on overriden __getattr__
  in the client to get params that not neccesarily need to
  be available (share_group_id and supports_share_migration)
- refactor ShareGroupTypeTests

Plus, enable py35 and py35dj20 jobs in tox and drop
old oslo-incubator files (install_venv.py)

Also add openstack-tox-py35 job to check python3 env.
openstack-tox-py35 should be defined in project-config later
but it is added to check python3 UT status.

Change-Id: I30582184904dc19e9cb4ca171b1fd2d161e09c48

commit_message:
Update tox.ini to stop using unverified package

As of pip 10.0, --allow-unverified is not permitted.

Use of the flag in this repo was previously used to force
installation of python-apt to accommodate certain unit tests.

The unverified package, python-apt, is no longer necessary
for test execution.

Change-Id: I3bb8af99cd8303c105f85a4712ca0b057994ef7d
Related-Bug: #1760720

commit_message:
WIP: ovs: Put switch port done before it's wired

Change interface driver to be put down on switch side when plug() driver
method is called. This is to avoid any traffic unwanted inboud or
outbound traffic for the port before it's properly wired by an L2 agent.
Also the port is left down in case binding fails for unexpected reason
instead of leaving attached port without local VLAN tag and hence in
trunk mode. Such ports were able to communicate among themselves when
binding failed or before the wiring was finished.

Closes-bug: #1767422

Change-Id: Icab78d6c34a76328409c5d90c3b5ad5536fbb88f

commit_message:
Do not create nova db user if database unchanged

This change prevents the task running if the database
has not been changed when a preconfigured external
database is not in use. This was the behaviour before
the preconfigured database feature was introduced.

Close-Bug: 1763375
Change-Id: I4f68905732dac75bc0deddab88047c9c0d7d65b5

commit_message:
Introduce new header for system-scoped tokens

Keystonemiddleware attempts to parse user/service tokens and populate
request headers for other services to consume. This information is
important for services looking to build oslo.context objects from
request environments.

Change-Id: I0717c2a5207a647999b4f9bcdf11f728984f0812
Closes-Bug: 1766731

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-05-04 07:58:27.000000000', 'message': 'Add support for remote consumers of Ceilometer event data.

There is a use-case to forward events received by ceilometer from
OpenStack services to an external system via http/udp. It comes
from the fact that aodh does not include all information about an
event alarm into POSTed data. Raw event data can be published by
ceilometer via http/udp to an external system without giving a
user direct access to rabbitmq.

This patch adds a context generator and associated templates and
configuration for configuring multiple event-sinks in
/etc/ceilometer/event_pipeline.yaml. Also adds support for future
Panko charm event consumer in the same context.

Closes Bug: 1763321

Change-Id: I931438c720272bd9a3d2b958ebabcd3584790bd0
'}, {'created': '2018-05-04 09:45:43.000000000', 'message': 'Add support for remote consumers of Ceilometer event data.

There is a use-case to forward events received by ceilometer from
OpenStack services to an external system via http/udp. It comes
from the fact that aodh does not include all information about an
event alarm into POSTed data. Raw event data can be published by
ceilometer via http/udp to an external system without giving a
user direct access to rabbitmq.

This patch adds a context generator, associated templates, and
configuration entry for configuring multiple event-sinks in
/etc/ceilometer/event_pipeline.yaml. This also modifies the
ceilometer.conf templates to reflect the correct naming of the
same file to align with upstream Ceilometer.

Also adds support for a future Panko charm event consumer using
the event-service interface in the above context with associated
metadata and hook symlinks.

This change will only effect Mitaka and later clouds.

Closes Bug: 1763321

Change-Id: I931438c720272bd9a3d2b958ebabcd3584790bd0

commit_message:
Add support for remote consumers of Ceilometer event data.

There is a use-case to forward events received by ceilometer from
OpenStack services to an external system via http/udp. It comes
from the fact that aodh does not include all information about an
event alarm into POSTed data. Raw event data can be published by
ceilometer via http/udp to an external system without giving a
user direct access to rabbitmq.

This patch adds a context generator, associated templates, and
configuration entry for configuring multiple event-sinks in
/etc/ceilometer/event_pipeline.yaml. This also modifies the
ceilometer.conf templates to reflect the correct naming of the
same file to align with upstream Ceilometer.

Also adds support for a future Panko charm event consumer using
the event-service interface in the above context with associated
metadata and hook symlinks.

This change will only effect Mitaka and later clouds.

Closes Bug: 1763321

Change-Id: I931438c720272bd9a3d2b958ebabcd3584790bd0

commit_message:
Add validation-errors-nonfatal in ceph upgrade.

Upstream CI job doesn't get to start the
ceph upgrade as the pre-validations are
failing in mistral. This patch adds the
--validation-errors-nonfatal when the
tripleo_upgrade_validations_non_fatal
parameters is set to true.

Change-Id: I7b4091a4603688b19669ff70afcfa852984a820e

commit_message:
Change template names to rocky

The new master branch should point now to rocky.

So, HOT templates should specify that they might contain features
for rocky release [1]

Also, this submission updates the yaml validation to use only latest
heat_version alias. There are cases in which we will need to set
the version for specific templates i.e. mixed versions, so there
is added a variable to assign specific templates to specific heat_version
aliases, avoiding the introductions of error by bulk replacing the
the old version in new releases.

[1]: https://docs.openstack.org/heat/latest/template_guide/hot_spec.html#rocky
Change-Id: Ib17526d9cc453516d99d4659ee5fa51a5aa7fb4b

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-04-13 11:00:19.000000000', 'message': 'Validate paths for tht templates dir vs env files

The --templates path must match the -e path, e.g:

openstack overcloud upgrade prepare \
  --templates ~/tripleo-heat-templates
  -e ~/tripleo-heat-templates/*.yaml

Though, there are totally valid cases when --templates is
mixed with auto generated -e files residing in either temp
dirs or the user's home dir. For example, heat undercloud
installer generates such files. So we can not blindly
prohibit non matching --templates and -e's.

To adress that UX issue, add additional contstraints for
overcloud and undercloud tht env files validation:

* "-e" files with abs paths not matching the given abs
  tht templates path shall not contain resource_registry.
* Only log a warning, when the non-matching path belongs
  to an env file w/o a resource_registry.

Closes-bug: #1762403

Change-Id: Ia9c62c787d6c581a66b2fde030a60499cfa18b82
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>
'}, {'created': '2018-04-24 15:23:41.000000000', 'message': 'UC: validate paths for tht templates and env files

The --templates path must match the -e path, e.g:

openstack overcloud upgrade prepare \
  --templates ~/tripleo-heat-templates
  -e ~/tripleo-heat-templates/*.yaml

Though, there are totally valid cases when --templates is
mixed with auto generated -e files residing in either temp
dirs or the user's home dir. For example, heat undercloud
installer generates such files. So we can not blindly
prohibit non matching --templates and -e's.

To adress that UX issue, add additional contstraints for
undercloud tht env files validation:

* "-e" files can not refer external files normally
  processed from jinja2 in t-h-t. Those must come from
  the templates path only.

NOTE: the similar change for overcloud should be done
in follow-ups.

The --templates path must match the -e path, e.g:

openstack overcloud upgrade prepare \
  --templates ~/tripleo-heat-templates
  -e ~/tripleo-heat-templates/*.yaml

Though, there are totally valid cases when --templates is

  the templates path only.

NOTE: the similar change for overcloud should be done
in follow-ups.

commit_message:
UC: validate paths for tht templates and env files

The --templates path must match the -e path, e.g:

openstack overcloud upgrade prepare \
  --templates ~/tripleo-heat-templates
  -e ~/tripleo-heat-templates/*.yaml

Though, there are totally valid cases when --templates is
mixed with auto generated -e files residing in either temp
dirs or the user's home dir. For example, heat undercloud
installer generates such files. So we can not blindly
prohibit non matching --templates and -e's.

To adress that UX issue, add additional contstraints for
undercloud tht env files validation:

* "-e" files can not refer external files normally
  processed from jinja2 in t-h-t. Those must come from
  the templates path only.

NOTE: the similar change for overcloud should be done
in follow-ups.

commit_message:
Add EnablePublicTLS flag

This flag is on by default, and serves to enable (or disable) the
public TLS by default feature.

It differs from the PublicSSLCertificateAutogenerated flag in the fact
that it works with mistral, while PublicSSLCertificateAutogenerated
works with certmonger in the overcloud.

Change-Id: If553ecff26d5ecd529c37ca438e0ba1795e9ecca

commit_message:
Find deployment name in config download

In some cases we get a ResourceGroup as parent resource of a deployment,
so the name will be a number. Ansible will be unhappy with that, so
let's get the grand parent to get the proper name.

Change-Id: Icc64b32a2179cd10853a54a83bf82a1761297ebd

commit_message:
Add config option for Barbican endpoint type

This change willl allow the user to specify the endpoint
type for Barbican.  The allowed values are: public, internal,
and admin.  The default value will be 'public' since this is
the current value.

Change-Id: Ic89519ed3a9c347a9fff245ec231aa575b42f1ac
Closes-bug: 1767473

"}, {'created': '2018-05-03 12:43:55.000000000', 'message': "Set normal CephAnsiblePlaybook on update/upgrade/ffwd converge

As we discovered bug #1768586 we'll need to make sure that every
parameter tweak in plan is followed by a stack update.

So far the Ceph upgrade command did set param -> stack update -> unset
param (only in plan). However this means the last CephAnsiblePlaybook
setting (back to normal deploy playbook) was discarded.

Let's reuse normal converge commands to converge CephAnsiblePlaybook
too, and we can remove the (now unused) ceph-upgrade-converge.yaml. We
won't do more stack updates than necessary, and at the same time the
user workflow stays somewhat consistent between envs that do and don't
have Ceph.

An alternative would be to run the as part of the Ceph command, but
that either means we'd have to run one more stack update then
necessary, or skip the last converge in envs with Ceph, and
essentially diverge further from the non-Ceph workflow.

Change-Id: If596531cbb1e750ed67e66391743f4c1833e4337

commit_message:
Set normal CephAnsiblePlaybook on update/upgrade/ffwd converge

As we discovered bug #1768586 we'll need to make sure that every
parameter tweak in plan is followed by a stack update.

So far the Ceph upgrade command did set param -> stack update -> unset
param (only in plan). However this means the last CephAnsiblePlaybook
setting (back to normal deploy playbook) was discarded.

Let's reuse normal converge commands to converge CephAnsiblePlaybook
too, and we can remove the (now unused) ceph-upgrade-converge.yaml. We
won't do more stack updates than necessary, and at the same time the
user workflow stays somewhat consistent between envs that do and don't
have Ceph.

An alternative would be to run the as part of the Ceph command, but
that either means we'd have to run one more stack update then
necessary, or skip the last converge in envs with Ceph, and
essentially diverge further from the non-Ceph workflow.

Change-Id: If596531cbb1e750ed67e66391743f4c1833e4337
Depends-On: I025eac40f8bda5f23c789e7fef1a9e9b49947f66
Partial-Bug: #1768586

commit_message:
Configure cors for glance for additional usability

In order to enable image uploads in horizon we need to configure several
things in glance, namely cors. This change implements default overrides
allowing the system to provide for direct image uploads through horizon
which will greatly improve our usability, especially for new users.

Change-Id: I19f4027dd30b0ba22cbb195c676802ce908d3e8f
Closes-Bug: #1747684

commit_message:
Fix dropped check for boot_index 0 in _validate_bdm

This reverts commit 7f4b49c9c97e06babf82f6846c804ad176cd4cde.

During refactor change I8a3e7e6c4b72eb1c3707d54049d18dc29f606fe5
the conditional that at least one BDM had to be the boot
device was inadvertantly dropped, presumably because there was
no test for that case.

The validation is added back here along with a test.

Change-Id: I299bf846b658f2bb6903c898d7deac748f8d90e4
Related-Bug: #1766306
(cherry picked from commit b9815c2331904a3749269289b861229796aa6c91)

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-02-01 19:51:01.000000000', 'message': "Use md5sum -b on images

according to md5sum man page

-b, --binary
      read in binary mode

The  sums  are  computed  as  described in RFC 1321.  When checking, the input
should be a former output of this program.  The default mode is to print a line
with checksum, a space, a character indicating input mode ('*' for binary, ' '
for text or where binary is insignificant), and name for each FILE.

the ramification is that this can be different if read binary is different from
from normal read on a given platform.  The binary option is better if you know
what you are trying to check is a binary blob.

Change-Id: Ib1490feefe4e026b3834a40ae9072a82af1379ee

commit_message:
Use md5sum -b on images

according to md5sum man page

-b, --binary
      read in binary mode

The  sums  are  computed  as  described in RFC 1321.  When checking, the input
should be a former output of this program.  The default mode is to print a line
with checksum, a space, a character indicating input mode ('*' for binary, ' '
for text or where binary is insignificant), and name for each FILE.

the ramification is that this can be different if read binary is different from
from normal read on a given platform.  The binary option is better if you know
what you are trying to check is a binary blob.

Change-Id: Ib1490feefe4e026b3834a40ae9072a82af1379ee

commit_message:
conf: Remove deprecated 'multi_instance_display_name_template' opt

This flag was deprecated in a previous cycle. The flag and any uses of
it can now be removed.

There is still a bit of simplification that can now be done around this
feature, but this is kept separate to avoid confusing matters.

Change-Id: I8ae8507a089df4d0a32be5fbc615e2166f44516e

commit_message:
[scenario] Add test case to check for RO access

Test if a compute instance with RO access granted to it via floating
IP address fails to write on the share. Also, add the capability to
pass the access level to the methods that allow access to shares.

Change-Id: I1aef8f1ed1b93c0847a6aa982f62c8e539d04337
Signed-off-by: Rishabh Dave <ridave@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Debian: fix barbican-api setup

Currently, it's not possible to use eventlet in Debian because the test
has been made on $::osfamily == 'Debian' instead of $::os_package_type.

Also, in Debian, the barbican-api service was never stopped before
configuring Apache, therefore, starting Apache just failed.

This patch also adds the $::barbican::params::api_service_name var if
using Debian packages.

Change-Id: Ide559f8fdc58ed3539325acd6696cec23c3de65b

commit_message:
Allow monkeypatching CONFIG_FILES

The patch to rip out the guts of os-client-config did not allow someone
to monkeypatch os_client_config.config.CONFIG_FILES. The nodepool test
suite was doing this - and so we're not sure who else might have been.

If we put the consumption of those into a wrapper constructor, we can
allow that to happen still.

Change-Id: Ibf676ecc9d28ee99d2bbfaccd9384b4ae590daf4

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-05-09 01:04:51.000000000', 'message': 'Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html

Change-Id: Ia8c279e170951441fcdf9f1ffc4a699a9da8c3fe
'}]
commit_message:
Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html

Change-Id: Ia8c279e170951441fcdf9f1ffc4a699a9da8c3fe

commit_message:
Remove Openstack and Ceph packages attempt 2

As we've switched to containers, it's time to start cleaning up the
packages we install on the overcloud images by default. This change
removes all the openstack and ceph packages from the
overcloud-controller, overcloud-ceph-storage and overcloud-compute
elements.

This reverts commit c69d6dd2c9d1c54d82669525bababc04b5a0688c. The
previous attempt was reverted due to an invalid json in the overcloud
pkg-map. This trailing comma has been addressed in this revert.

Change-Id: I5ceb329e18024040697ad5eab892d13c51ad276f
Related-Blueprint: cleanup-overcloud-images

commit_message:
Enforce removal of container network namespace.

This patch enforces the removal of the container
network namespace when the environment is destroyed.

Closes-Bug: #1769651

Change-Id: I9b0bbbb5a59e6067a745635c555051ef97b79f9a
Signed-off-by: Jorge Niedbalski <jorge.niedbalski@linaro.org>
(cherry picked from commit 6c5a6c65f11008b484551267e24ee04e73280232)

This patchset adds "also-notifies" option which is an optional part
of the "pools.yaml" configuration and should only be used to define
DNS servers other than the backend servers which should receive
notifications on zone changes.

commit_message:
Add "also-notifies" option

This patchset adds "also-notifies" option which is an optional part
of the "pools.yaml" configuration and should only be used to define
DNS servers other than the backend servers which should receive
notifications on zone changes.

Change-Id: I10faa6ec4ea4fd1f1f17c7234662cd5c23624c1d
Closes-Bug: 1758008

commit_message:
Properly set vios_ids when discovering initiator

If vios_ids were not passed to discover_initiator, they get set to
a list of vioses instead of a list of the ids.

Change-Id: If4e2329022f4fb9b81c7b64238defc256bc00f66
Closes-bug: 1769919

commit_message:
Reinstate testing of changes to requirements.txt

Change I0c1328237d2109b1d1d5dcb40f331fff1ab10257 recently prevented
running kolla deployment CI jobs against changes to some files,
including requirements.txt. This change reinstates testing of changes to
requirements.txt, since this can have an effect on the operation of
kolla ansible.

Change-Id: I3d839de9aed60cddebea7d1140f618d3261cca2a

commit_message:
Remove ironic_host_manager usage

The baremetal scheduling options were deprecated
in Pike and the ironic_host_manager was deprecated
in Queens and has now been removed. Deployments
must use resource classes now for baremetal scheduling.

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/565805/
Change-Id: I2f3e2821c4c6c68e378816ffc38f863394a45963

commit_message:
Add 'enable-notifications-designate' option

This patchset addss 'enable-notifications-designate' option which
enables 'notifications_designate' notification topic. The topic
should be only enabled in legacy deployments which use notification
topics for the purpose of integrating designate with nova and
neutron.

Change-Id: I1bed2327bf351cd0e56c657dd028ec26a4b68d60
Closes-Bug: #1659943

commit_message:
Revert "Set optional API version-related environment vars"

This reverts commit 6d369703bb1778a11cf55fe679150928cb553cf6.
Before that commit, puppet-openstack was writing in /root/openrc:
export OS_IDENTITY_VERSION=3.1

Since this patch, it doesn't anymore, and everything in Debian is
completely broken: keystone bootstraping fails, image listing fails, etc.

I very much would enjoy having the feature of the reverted patch, but it
should never change the default behavior of setting OS_IDENTITY_VERSION.
I attempted to change the current behavior, keeping this patch, but
failed, so I suggest the original committer to just come back with a
better patch later on, once it's been reverted.

Change-Id: If833e6c9fe7d463e6270ef272295341bbf4c2570

[{'created': '2018-05-09 07:13:43.000000000', 'message': 'Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html

commit_message:
Fix the gate jobs

This patch is including two patches to fix the gate.

Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html
(cherry picked from commit ccd542f7ea26d792ca8a07539f66fac6dfddbfb9)

Fix deploy-guide links

Deploy guides includes quickstart guide.
Includes respect relative paths, but when
quickstart includes vagrant doc, deploy-guide
tries to locate the doc in its doctree (deploy-guide/source).

This causes error 404 and deploy-guide post-gates to fail
(cherry picked from commit 197a264a3b772f9d6c9c9775bf00357e2a7a9a10)

Change-Id: I05790c5f946a4127fe6c8d9867cc618cb83d67fb

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary BRs for keystone

Remove following not required BRs for keystone:-
- tempest
- os-api-ref
- reno
- python-subunit
- oslosphinx

Also add "openstackdocstheme" BR for docs and "which" for
tests.
"openstackdocstheme" was indirectly included by os-api-ref
and "which" by tempest before this patch.

Change-Id: Iebb73452d4a168f7469713b7f7afa71230988ff8

commit_message:
Retry restarting systemd-journald

It is possible that systemd-journald fails to properly restart on
the first attempt due to assertion errors similar to the following:

  Assertion 'f' failed at src/journal/journal-file.c:132,
  function journal_file_close(). Aborting.

However, the service eventually starts with no problems, so we can
simply retry which will let it restart cleanly on the next attempt.

Change-Id: Ic65466b0d339c5a1b476e91483beca248ed0a02d
(cherry picked from commit 66ed618bce2c56a36e803d43ba6695dc3d64f0f3)

commit_message:
Add designate-bind monitoring capability

This patch modifies Bind to listen also on localhost for rndc commands
so that monitoring agents can poll for status, and configuring Bind
to post statistical data in named.stats file.

	modified:   src/templates/named.conf
	modified:   src/templates/named.conf.options

Closes-Bug: #1752611

commit_message:
Add binary installation for PIP

This patch adds support in order to be able to install PIP from
the upstream repo.  Due to the fact that most binary deployemnts
currently ship some iteration of pip 8.x, change the integration
checks to make sure that we have pip 8.x rather than a pinned
version

Depends-On: I21d18b21b22ed263682477e50992eba9ebd00798
Change-Id: If3079823ad1ed7998dc5c91c554c78cdc99fffa5

commit_message:
Add Glance installation from binary

This patch adds support to install Glance from RDO with a few
differences from source installs

- Binary deploys don't install systemd files
- Binary deploys use upstream recommended deployment method
- Therefore, RDO installs will not use UWSGI.

Depends-On: If3079823ad1ed7998dc5c91c554c78cdc99fffa5
Change-Id: Ic5de80f92b04f279643d3a8a205da5fbe3a8bb63

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-04-20 07:33:52.000000000', 'message': 'Using assertIsNone() instead of assertEqual(None)

Following OpenStack Style Guidelines:
[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#unit-tests-and-assertraises
[H203] Unit test assertions tend to give better messages for more specific
assertions. As a result, assertIsNone(...) is preferred over
assertEqual(None, ...) and assertIs(..., None)

Change-Id: Ib5dcf2f389dd76f99d87ad22268695f2a702e6b3
'}]
commit_message:
Using assertIsNone() instead of assertEqual(None)

Following OpenStack Style Guidelines:
[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#unit-tests-and-assertraises
[H203] Unit test assertions tend to give better messages for more specific
assertions. As a result, assertIsNone(...) is preferred over
assertEqual(None, ...) and assertIs(..., None)

Change-Id: Ib5dcf2f389dd76f99d87ad22268695f2a702e6b3

commit_message:
Ensure that comments are not counted

With the previous grep, it was possible that any commented nameserver
entries would be counted.  This patch fixes that.

Change-Id: I9925cb9a71c1b58dcf12f70d8ce0872386732f06
Closes-Bug: #1768725

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-04-26 11:13:57.000000000', 'message': 'Add broker support for passing app_name

In Ceph >= Luminous, application name needs to be set
on a per-pool level to avoid health warnings. This
change adds support for sending the application name
over the broker channel from consuming charms.

When a name is not sent from the other side of the
relation, the application name will be set to "unknown"
in Luminous and greater

Change-Id: I1109251b08da20adaf3d677c38fc1aacfba29439
Closes-Bug: #1753640
Depends-On: I99ae47b6802f50ea019751ffa328f11567cca567
'}, {'created': '2018-04-26 11:22:53.000000000', 'message': 'Add broker support for passing app_name

In Ceph >= Luminous, application name needs to be set
on a per-pool level to avoid health warnings. This
change adds support for sending the application name
over the broker channel from consuming charms.

When a name is not sent from the other side of the

commit_message:
Add broker support for passing app_name

In Ceph >= Luminous, application name needs to be set
on a per-pool level to avoid health warnings. This
change adds support for sending the application name
over the broker channel from consuming charms.

When a name is not sent from the other side of the
relation, the application name will be set to "unknown"
in Luminous and greater

Change-Id: I1109251b08da20adaf3d677c38fc1aacfba29439
Closes-Bug: #1753640
Depends-On: I99ae47b6802f50ea019751ffa328f11567cca567

commit_message:
Handle PortNotFoundClient exception when getting ports

There could be a race between deleting an instance and retrieving its
port groups from Neutron. In this case PortNotFoundClient is raised and
it can be safely ignored.

Change-Id: I31c9ea8628c6f3985f8e9118d9687bbfb8789b68
Closes-Bug: #1767058

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-02-21 20:40:08.000000000', 'message': 'Relocate libvirt-sock from /run to /home

On one of the local test systems, quickstart.sh aborts when
trying to run "openstack overcloud node introspect" (in task
overcloud-prep-images). This happens because the VirtualBMC
service fails to start (virtualbmc@control_0.service etc.).
The service fails because it tests if the supplied URL for
libvirt is useable, and it's not. An access to it fails because
/run/user/1000 does not exist on the host.

Our speculation is that normally, we log in to stack@virthost
and run virsh, which starts libvirtd. The logging-in makes the
systemd-logind mount /run/user/1000, which is normal. When we
log out, libvirtd keeps the socket open and thus /run/user/1000
continues to exist. However, the system in question is so slow,
that libvirtd gets bored and exits, and systemd-logind umounts
the directory. When VBMC comes around to probe, the ssh connection
for qemu+ssh:// does not trigger systemd-logind and the directory
/run/user/1000 does not exist, which makes the proble to abort.

This is associated with "su - stack" not mounting /run/user/1000
(although ssh stack@virthost does so). It's a separate story why
that happens, the files in /etc/pam.d/ appear to require it
working, but something prevents it.

The fix or workaround for now is to avoid /run/user/1000 and
use the /home/stack/.cache, at least as long as we support
RHEL 7 and CentOS 7.

Change-Id: I92b5f0cc5f02aee275d80f41cb8fc920df6b1e14
'}]
commit_message:
Relocate libvirt-sock from /run to /home

On one of the local test systems, quickstart.sh aborts when
trying to run "openstack overcloud node introspect" (in task
overcloud-prep-images). This happens because the VirtualBMC
service fails to start (virtualbmc@control_0.service etc.).
The service fails because it tests if the supplied URL for
libvirt is useable, and it's not. An access to it fails because
/run/user/1000 does not exist on the host.

Our speculation is that normally, we log in to stack@virthost
and run virsh, which starts libvirtd. The logging-in makes the
systemd-logind mount /run/user/1000, which is normal. When we
log out, libvirtd keeps the socket open and thus /run/user/1000
continues to exist. However, the system in question is so slow,
that libvirtd gets bored and exits, and systemd-logind umounts
the directory. When VBMC comes around to probe, the ssh connection
for qemu+ssh:// does not trigger systemd-logind and the directory
/run/user/1000 does not exist, which makes the proble to abort.

This is associated with "su - stack" not mounting /run/user/1000
(although ssh stack@virthost does so). It's a separate story why
that happens, the files in /etc/pam.d/ appear to require it
working, but something prevents it.

The fix or workaround for now is to avoid /run/user/1000 and
use the /home/stack/.cache, at least as long as we support
RHEL 7 and CentOS 7.

commit_message:
Decouple release from overcloud_release

Our workarounds were using release variable which defines
version of undercloud not overcloud. We need to make sure
we do overcloud workarounds on overcloud_release and
undercloud workarounds on release.

Change-Id: Id58685f2dca5821f0b1a7ee0da23e630bd6e6f49

commit_message:
revist lifecycle_hook logic

    1. use one "Message" object to sink event
    2. add physical_id which is the actual to the event message
    3. check both node status and physical id before send event
    4. remove the actions that can be executed immediately from "child"
    to reduce DB interactions

Change-Id: Ie34fa1a44b575644685dc400fd70deb160c5c2e5

commit_message:
Make UI accessable by default on OVB

A recent OVB commit[1] opens port 3000 and adds a stack output for the
private IP of the undercloud server.

This change uses that to bind the UI to the private IP of the
undercloud so that the UI can be accessed via
http://<floating ip>:3000

This change also makes the OVB git repo a variable so that local
development of OVB changes is easier.

[1] https://github.com/cybertron/openstack-virtual-baremetal/commit/1b6f33ab08ec29892ac557d3b1d318ef3fb4dc27

Change-Id: Ib51a038331d3d86da74af9f8c904d9a282087da0
Closes-Bug: #1719490

subject: Allow OVB to attach undercloud to existing floating IP

commit_message:
Allow OVB to attach undercloud to existing floating IP

Currently a different floating IP is created for every OVB deployment,
but it is convenient for development environments to allow for having
a stable IP for accessing the undercloud.

This change adds the undercloud_floating_ip and
undercloud_floating_ip_id parameters so that OVB
undercloud-floating-existing environment can be used as an alternative
to the default undercloud-floating.

Change-Id: Iad7e9e3c4da717fea28ec20e1d290a2510481a06

commit_message:
use virthost_user instead of non_root_user

in order to avoid confusion about which user is being used where,
tripleo-quickstart has replaced non_root_user with virthost_user and
undercloud_user.  This commit implements the same changes in
tripleo-quickstart-extras.

Change-Id: Ib68815660a633a987b80ea5e45627c0aa01c96f3

commit_message:
Remove overcloud_services default value

...and document the expected structure in README instead.

This default value would not result in creating a sensible overcloud
deployment, and as such was not useful as a default. Also, replicating
the tripleo-heat-templates default here and keeping it in sync would be
a needless maintenance chore. Therefore should simply remove the
default.

If the user wants to set composable_services: true, they should also set
their own overcloud_services list. If they forget to do so, OOOQ should
fail.

The default case is already handled well by defaulting
composable_services to false. In that case we don't use
overcloud_services variable at all and the default set of services is
taken from what tripleo-heat-templates define.

Change-Id: I39dcee5b41fd430475ff87a5628c7c4b0ecbd762

commit_message:
WIP: Give build-test-packages role the option to inject

This commit gives the build-test-packages role a new option: to specify
a package to be built in addition to sourcing from Zuul and Jenkins.
This would primarily be used to replicate failures and test fixes in a
CI scenario.

Change-Id: Ic74b52008c3ebaabecaf7e019013e5cf634654e8

commit_message:
Switch to Tempest run cli for running tempest

* tempest run command does not having *tempest_until_failure*
  flag. So it needs to be removed also.

* Currently ostestr is switched to stestr which breaks the stuff.
  It is better to switched to tempest run in order to avoid the
  effect.

Change-Id: Id7cbf37e9e98811271410d0ea04c87d5299c83e7

commit_message:
WIP: Add stack update role

This commit provides a role to run stack update operations and change
overcloud parameters. This will be useful for testing vairous
overcloud settings change possibilities in a CI setting.

Example usage:

- name: Run stack update with compute updates
  hosts: undercloud
  vars:
    - update_compute_nodes: true
  roles:
    - update-stack

Change-Id: I765c4d11da5f34c449cbcdcba97567f515d7051d

commit_message:
Use clean keystone URL in the keystone validation

Inventory variable overcloud_keystone_url gets its
value from stack's output 'KeystoneURL'
which might include the keystone version.
We need to get rid off the version, otherwise
undercloud validations fail at the time of
checking the Keystone endpoint [0].

[0] - https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-validations/blob/545e4924e30769eb06100be1b5b2cd64637cf76e/validations/openstack-endpoints.yaml#L28

Co-Authored-By: Jose Luis Franco <jfrancoa@redhat.com>
Story: #2001897

Change-Id: I3e900afd840a4a0504a573a1eabe80911f8f7881
(cherry picked from commit c8cefbd9e97e84c0525259d93256c26069bc4a95)

[{'created': '2017-09-10 06:52:37.000000000', 'message': 'DNR WIP Initial autofencing iptables support

This is an initial WIP to get oooq setup to configure autofencing.
It requires Ie3d9d524980f9b257042c0fea77a37a56c04abd4 in
instack-undercloud to be applied before running the undercloud install.
The dependant change-Id is on oooq and will set up the
fencing_config.yaml. In this change we open up iptables on the
undercloud so that the overcloud can actually talk ipmi to the vbmc.

Depends-On: I747a24eda7dd9ef7aa32e3113569edebb90239a8
Change-Id: Ia5a6e3b6ee328b290127e2842ff27effe6f786ee
'}, {'created': '2017-10-03 20:13:19.000000000', 'message': "WIP Initial autofencing support

With this change we introduce the 'enable_autofencing' parameter which
defaults to false. When enabled we create a fencing_config.yaml file
which contains all the necessary information for the overcloud to
configure IPMI-based stonith devices.

In order for the virtualbmc IPMI ports to be reachable we also create
an iptables rule to open up those ports for the overcloud.

NB: Is because I need to do some more tests end-to-end.

commit_message:
Autofencing support

With this change we introduce the 'enable_autofencing' parameter which
defaults to false. When enabled we create a fencing_config.yaml file
which contains all the necessary information for the overcloud to
configure IPMI-based stonith devices.

In order for the virtualbmc IPMI ports to be reachable we also create
an iptables rule to open up those ports for the overcloud.

With this option on, we correctly get stonith autoconfigured:
[root@overcloud-controller-0 ~]# pcs stonith
 stonith-fence_ipmilan-00b723a39acb (stonith:fence_ipmilan): Started overcloud-controller-0
 stonith-fence_ipmilan-00b723a39ac7 (stonith:fence_ipmilan): Started overcloud-controller-1
 stonith-fence_ipmilan-00b723a39ac3 (stonith:fence_ipmilan): Started overcloud-controller-2

Depends-On: I0727a9224b5e9eaafaa374ecfbcd4fb9ccb52d58

commit_message:
Use 'cat' instead of 'echo' to create file

An empty file (validate-template-override.yaml)
will be created when using 'echo', which in turn
causes pingtest fail.

Change-Id: I18552b406610c3c03635e04c63eaae688575a647

> https://review.openstack.org/#/c/491170/ don't fix the problem with
 > tempest return status? According comment in https://bugs.launchpad.net/tripleo/+bug/1708793:
 > 
 > When the options --pretty are used the script will fail
 > appropriately

Yes, the above patch fixes the status. But the way we are determining the tempest status is based on time stamp of tempest run script.
But when we say about tempest status to true it means that there is no failed tests else false if we have failed status.

So i think we can use testr failing --lists in order to determine tempest status instead of timestamp. If tempest will fail it will return a list of failied tests in ansible console log."}, {'account_id': 12393, 'date': '2017-08-14 12:31:36.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2: Patch Set 1 was rebased.'}, {'account_id': 8367, 'date': '2017-08-14 12:43:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I did not understand, the tempest status isn't based on timestamp, it's based on the result of ostestr, which is the same way that is handled in other projects. Also, I'm completely against pollute more than already is the console log.
As we talked, if I want to see the list of failures, I'll go straight to tempest.html file that is now in the root of /logs directory, and there I can see what fail, and the reason."}, {'account_id': 12393, 'date': '2017-08-14 13:00:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

> I did not understand, the tempest status isn't based on timestamp,
 > it's based on the result of ostestr, which is the same way that is
 > handled in other projects. 
https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-quickstart-extras/blob/master/roles/validate-tempest/tasks/run-tempest.yml#L5 is used to determine tempest status based on logging the run tempest script.

 > Also, I'm completely against pollute
 > more than already is the console log.

I am not seeing how it is polluting. from the current code, if tempest status is failed, it prints the traceback of the failed tests in the console log but my changes will be showing the list of failed tests and proper exit status getting registered.

commit_message:
Use testr failing --list to determine tempest status

* on running testr failing --list exit status will return 0
  if all the tests are passed and if any tests has failed. It will
  list failing tests and exit status will be 1.

* It is the best way to determine the tempest run status.

Change-Id: I5d3230368463ce40114541a5eda409b49df8d360

commit_message:
Support release change during playbook run

Sometimes it's neeeded to change release of tripleo distribution
during the run (in upgrades for example), this patch add suppoort
for this:
 - Remove enforcing of release from quickstart.sh
 - Move default release to repo-setup role
 - Use include_vars in repo-setup role for loading release vars,
   passing var "release_config" to role will define which release
   file will be included.
 - Continue support of -R|--release argument in quickstart, it will
   remain for backward compatibility and running playbooks with one
   release only.

Change-Id: Ia62281c232e6ccaee4feaeb01b5c9a122350bf64

commit_message:
Allow customizing the hard-drive Serial and/or WWN

This patch allows specifying a disk Serial and/or WWN for the overcloud
VMs. Ironic has a feature called "root device hints" which allows
operators to use disk attributes such as: model, size, serial, wwn,
etc... to specify which disk the image should be deployed onto.

By allowing it to be specified we can then exercise this feature from
Ironic with tripleo-quickstart.

This patch also changes the default disk controller from virtio to scsi
in the overcloud nodes because such attributes are not part of virtio in
libvirt.

Co-Authored-By: Dmitry Tantsur <dtantsur@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I4d862ee0c16f679a117c20201c6a884224586b25
Closes-Bug: #1645673

commit_message:
Decouple release from overcloud_release

Our workarounds were using release variable which defines
version of undercloud not overcloud. We need to make sure
we do overcloud workarounds on overcloud_release and
undercloud workarounds on release.

Change-Id: Ibcf65485e5f1793a4b005bee73e0d42925b3a442

commit_message:
Enable the image signing feature in scenario 2

Adding this tempest option will force python-tempestconf to
create signed images in the test environment.  This is needed
so that tests will continue to pass when glance signature
vverification is enabled in nova.

Depends-On: I7186e5904bf5c4843b85436c2d081e50007931ff
Change-Id: Ie62025da5bd3ea495ef706f2cd18860a94c27e16

[{'created': '2017-02-28 16:54:32.000000000', 'message': 'modify basic test to use non-default non_root_user

we expect operators to be able to set non_root_user in their
configuration, but we do not respect this value in our playbooks.
This modifies basic.sh to us  a non-default value for non_root_user to
flush out these issues.

Change-Id: I98487b98fea5f6549790bebb4da744d07f68eed3
'}]
commit_message:
modify basic test to use non-default non_root_user

we expect operators to be able to set non_root_user in their
configuration, but we do not respect this value in our playbooks.
This modifies basic.sh to us  a non-default value for non_root_user to
flush out these issues.

Change-Id: I98487b98fea5f6549790bebb4da744d07f68eed3

commit_message:
Remove [scheduler]/host_manager config option

While this option itself was not technically deprecated,
the option only had two choices and the "ironic_host_manager"
choice has been deprecated since Queens:

  Iebc74a09990dcda8cf0ee2a41f9ae1058d2a182a

And was removed in Rocky:

  I695b250c82c8dcedcd8e2bee00c56bb2df19212c

Since the host_manager option only had one choice, which
is also the default, it's not really an option anymore and
we can simply remove it. Setting it will have no effect
so there should be no upgrade impact for its removal.

Change-Id: Ic61ae3a4f563aa54a3a2956667c702a81e610fc3

Rename objectstorage flavor to swift-storage

Actually it's called swift-storage in TripleO, and it makes sense to use
the same name within TripleO quickstart to simplify testing.

Also add a Swift config to simplify testing.

Change-Id: I48358ab8e5f5445e6ba6e87f782d503645f64ae9

commit_message:
improve generated ssh configuration

When deploying an environment using a pre-existing inventory, the
quickstart could produce incorrect ssh configuration files because the
conditions in the templates would key off the presence or absence of
things like the ansible_host and ansible_user variables, which may not
existing for simple inventories.

This patch introduces sane defaults in the absence of those variables.

Change-Id: I955aa3db0ba21e8360ecf5c058009810680fbd92
Closes-bug: #1631125
Closes-bug: #1631124

commit_message:
restore support for multiple deployments on virthost

some confusion has developed in the tripleo-quickstart involving user
names and working directories, resulting in a situation that worked
only because we were defaulting to identical values on both the
virthost and the undercloud.  when attemping to deploy multiple
tripleo-quickstart environments under different user ids on the same
virthost this would cause the deployment to fail.

this changes attempts to cleanly separate those concerns:

- instead of the nebulous names "non_root_user" and "ssh_user", we now
  have "virthost_user" and "undercloud_user".

- we have "virthost_working_dir" and "undercloud_working_dir"

- some tasks have been relocated from provision to libvirt/setup,
  reflecting the fact that they need to run per-remote-user rather
  than per-remote-host

Change-Id: Ib1d4177ca54ef341a92d3b3d7b637922d572b31d
Closes-bug: #1631119
Closes-bug: #1631120

exclude python-dns from delorean-pike-testing

The python-dns package listed in the delorean-pike-testing repository
prevents installation of the latest version from centos-base (due to
repo priorities).

Closes-bug: #1717550

commit_message:
neutron, nova: fixed multiple mechanism drivers support

Done:
- removed network.backed which is duplicate to ml2 mechanism drivers
- fixed not to mount unnecessary config files for dhcp, l3, and metadata agents
- added a new node label indicating what kind of l2 agent to run
- set interface_driver based on the new node label
  (fixed interface_driver not to take multiple values)
- fixed dependency for nova-compute, dhcp-agent, l3-agent and metadata-agent
  by ensuring l2 agent pod is running locally
- minor changes on values.yaml

To Do:
- consider the case where normal and direct(sriov) ports reside on the same node
- eliminate assumptions on core_plugin=ml2

Change-Id: I42d647e361dea75082173244637b4ef18f8b1b99

commit_message:
tox.ini: Use python3.5 in py35 environment

When stuff fails it tends to fail in different ways on different
versions of python. It's very unhelpful if 'tox -epy35' means a
different thing on every developer's machine, which is what tends to
happen if you use python3 as the basepython.

Change-Id: I4f92cd6bb22e36b1c49436eca1849712682aec68

commit_message:
Remove ironic_host_manager usage

The baremetal scheduling options were deprecated
in Pike and the ironic_host_manager was deprecated
in Queens and has now been removed. Deployments
must use resource classes now for baremetal scheduling.

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/565805/
Change-Id: I46fd53fe70c4e63e5b06043bd650a2d6dc7e9ff1

Remove disable-workflow-tasks.yaml env

Once workflow_tasks are removed from the ceph templates, we no longer
need to include the environment to explicitly disable them.

commit_message:
conf: Resolve TODOs in 'database'

These are self-explanatory, with some exceptions:

- IntOpt does not take a 'choices' parameter
- 'connection' cannot have a 'required' parameter as not all nodes
  need it and it would break upgrades
- Some of the defaults suggested weren't actually defaults in oslo.db

Change-Id: Id3bb4224a30f2abe26c89af6bc5546127c4db739

commit_message:
objects: remove pagesize from __init__ of InstanceNUMATopology

Removes the initialization of pagesize to None when creating new
instances of InstanceNUMATopology. This necessitates checking for the
presence of the field before using it. The current pattern allowed us to
avoid this check, at the expense of not being able to inspect objects
easily and consistently generate a list of fields.

As part of this change, a bug in tests for overcommitting of NUMA cells
was uncovered. The tests are reworked to resolve this and documentation
added in case people find the feature as confusing as I did initially.

Change-Id: I11392bb5bcb4427faae3cb8bba2d615271203e81
Co-Authored-By: Sahid Orentino Ferdjaoui <sahid.ferdjaoui@redhat.com>

commit_message:
objects: remove related pinning from __init__ of InstanceNUMATopology

Removes the initialization of 'cpu_pinning', 'cpu_policy' and
'cpu_thread_policy' when creating object InstanceNUMATopology. The
current pattern allowed us to avoid some checks but meant we could
easily inspect objects and consistently generate a list of fields. This
also allows us to fix two bugs:

- Fix backwards compatibility for InstanceNUMACell

  Pre-1.3 versions of InstanceNUMACell didn't have a 'cpu_policy' field.
  However, after this, the 'cpu_pinning_requested' function was changed
  to rely on this variable. This is resolved through the reinstatement
  of the pre-1.3 check for pre-1.3 objects versions.

- Fix a faulty unit test

  We should check 'nova_object.data', not the primitive itself.

Change-Id: Iac4c6895c7059fa095906304a7e74c0c89057cd2
Co-Authored-By: Sahid Orentino Ferdjaoui <sahid.ferdjaoui@redhat.com>
Resolves-bug: #1636338

commit_message:
objects: remove cpuset_reserved from __init__ of InstanceNUMATopology

This commit removes the initialization of cpuset_reserved to None when
creating object InstanceNUMATopology. The current pattern allowed us to
avoid some checks but meant we could inspect objects easily and
consistently generate a list of fields.

Change-Id: I31937b288a9549341426d2e619aae39b3e8550c7

[{'created': '2018-04-24 04:34:00.000000000', 'message': 'Fix builddoc with sphinx <= 1.6

I went to build infra-specs which specifies sphinx==1.5.6 and hit

 Traceback (most recent call last):
   File "setup.py", line 29, in <module>
     pbr=True)
   ...
  File ".../pbr/builddoc.py", line 235, in run
    self._sphinx_run()
  File ".../pbr/builddoc.py", line 162, in _sphinx_run
    freshenv=self.fresh_env, warningiserror=self.warning_is_error)
  File ".../sphinx/application.py", line 244, in __init__
    self._init_builder(self.buildername)
  File "...//sphinx/application.py", line 311, in _init_builder
    raise SphinxError('Builder name %s not registered' % buildername)
 sphinx.errors.SphinxError: Builder name h not registered

It appears to be a typo introduced with
I18bbf693bca2f6e49d822ae2940d2170a2b90ce9; make sure we're walking the
self.builders list; not the string self.builder.

commit_message:
Fix builddoc with sphinx <= 1.6

I went to build infra-specs which specifies sphinx==1.5.6 and hit

 Traceback (most recent call last):
   File "setup.py", line 29, in <module>
     pbr=True)
   ...
  File ".../pbr/builddoc.py", line 235, in run
    self._sphinx_run()
  File ".../pbr/builddoc.py", line 162, in _sphinx_run
    freshenv=self.fresh_env, warningiserror=self.warning_is_error)
  File ".../sphinx/application.py", line 244, in __init__
    self._init_builder(self.buildername)
  File "...//sphinx/application.py", line 311, in _init_builder
    raise SphinxError('Builder name %s not registered' % buildername)
 sphinx.errors.SphinxError: Builder name h not registered

It appears to be a typo introduced with
I18bbf693bca2f6e49d822ae2940d2170a2b90ce9; make sure we're walking the
self.builders list; not the string self.builder.

Change-Id: Ic038029c361b3ede48f2b495c74430d3ad1eab82

commit_message:
Add ssh-user to get_tripleo_ansible_inventory

We were missing --ssh-user when calling
get_tripleo_ansible_inventory assigning
overcloud as the ssh_user by default.

This is failing after adding the --stack option
as he had only one before

Closes-Bug: 1767379

commit_message:
Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html

Change-Id: I05790c5f946a4127fe6c8d9867cc618cb83d67fb
(cherry picked from commit ccd542f7ea26d792ca8a07539f66fac6dfddbfb9)

commit_message:
Fix the gate jobs

This patch including two backport commits.

Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html
(cherry picked from commit ccd542f7ea26d792ca8a07539f66fac6dfddbfb9)

Fix deploy-guide links

Deploy guides includes quickstart guide.
Includes respect relative paths, but when
quickstart includes vagrant doc, deploy-guide
tries to locate the doc in its doctree (deploy-guide/source).

This causes error 404 and deploy-guide post-gates to fail

(cherry picked from commit 197a264a3b772f9d6c9c9775bf00357e2a7a9a10)

Change-Id: I05790c5f946a4127fe6c8d9867cc618cb83d67fb

commit_message:
Take control of when `ceph-create-keys` is run

For Ceph versions prior to Luminous the `ceph-create-keys`
is run by the init system in conjunction with starting the
ceph-mon service.

At some point during the Hammer lifetime a hard coded timeout
of 600 seconds was added:
https://github.com/ceph/ceph/commit/8bab74537f5891f2b97f0fb6722e2e00416b723a

In many circumstances this is not enough.  With this commit
we take control of running this command.

__NOTE__ it is important that charms deploying the ceph-mon
disable running of `ceph-create-keys` from the init system.

From Luminous and onwards we can use the newly added --timeout
flag.  For previous versions we rely on retry_on_exception
decorator.

Change-Id: I3d3c7298076730c423ca5cc059316619f415b885
Related-Bug: #1719436

commit_message:
Add test Migrating a volume from created snapshot

This patch is uploaded, since there was a bug while
migrating/retyping a volume created from snapshot to a
different backend after snapshot got deleted.

Related-Bug: #1697527
Change-Id: Idd276414c45c07dfd27ba58c309db5a73029a5cc

commit_message:
Fix sphinx-docs job

build-openstack-sphinx-docs jobs fail on all branches due to the new
pip version 10 introduces some previously Warning as Error: in case of
calling "pip install" without any package name, the command fails.
tox_install.sh is called during docs job without any package passed to pip.

This patch is necessary until the tox_install.sh removal [1] is merged in.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/555788

'}, {'created': '2018-03-12 12:30:00.000000000', 'message': 'Generate and mount wrappers for dnsmasq and keepalived

The neutron agents use dnsmasq and keepalived as part of their
implementation. Running these "subprocesses" in separate containers
prevent dataplane breakages/unnecessary failover on agent container
restart. This patch triggers the creation and mounting of wrappers
for launching these processes in containers.

Closes-Bug: #1749209
Depends-On: Icd4c24ac686d957391548a04722266cefc1bce27
Change-Id: Iea53489c916765bcfd88d7d12e6a32e1b6276d81

commit_message:
Generate and mount wrappers for neutron agent processes

The neutron agents use things like dnsmasq and keepalived as part of
their implementation. Running these "subprocesses" in separate
containers prevent dataplane breakages/unnecessary failover on agent
container restart. This patch triggers the creation and mounting of
wrappers for launching these processes in containers.

Related-Bug: #1749209
Depends-On: Icd4c24ac686d957391548a04722266cefc1bce27
Depends-On: I8d93f4eccde1dc6e55e10399184ee80671355769

commit_message:
Avoid running kolla source jobs for unnecessary  files

While fixing test-requirement.txt, I found that
check pipeline can be more optimized in term of selecting
the jobs to run based on file change.
- https://review.openstack.org/#/c/567083/
kolla main jobs are not needed to be run on check
pipeline for test-requirements.txt, releasenotes/* etc.

This commit skip those jobs when only above files
are changed in patch. This is will save time as well
as infra resource also.

Change-Id: I0c1328237d2109b1d1d5dcb40f331fff1ab10257

commit_message:
Updated tests on bug, when get list returns deleted items

In I4d2f44fa149aee564c62a69822c6ad79de5bba8a we introduced new
_get_model_list method that introduces unify way for retrieving models
from db. This commit adds tests that do checks on bug 1761956, when
selecting with filter() method could return deleted entites.

Change-Id: I12df4af70bcc25654a0fb276ea7145d772d891e2
Related-Bug: 1761956

subject: Fix the gate with backport packages
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-05-09 08:30:18.000000000', 'message': 'Fix the gate with backport packages

This patch is including two patches to fix the gate.

Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html
(cherry picked from commit 197a264a3b772f9d6c9c9775bf00357e2a7a9a10)

Fix deploy-guide links

Deploy guides includes quickstart guide.
Includes respect relative paths, but when
quickstart includes vagrant doc, deploy-guide
tries to locate the doc in its doctree (deploy-guide/source).

This causes error 404 and deploy-guide post-gates to fail
(cherry picked from commit ccd542f7ea26d792ca8a07539f66fac6dfddbfb9)

Change-Id: I05e49bbcef564ad4f3d80f0649ccf191d9f8b59d
'}]
commit_message:
Fix the gate with backport packages

This patch is including two patches to fix the gate.

Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html
(cherry picked from commit 197a264a3b772f9d6c9c9775bf00357e2a7a9a10)

Fix deploy-guide links

Deploy guides includes quickstart guide.
Includes respect relative paths, but when
quickstart includes vagrant doc, deploy-guide
tries to locate the doc in its doctree (deploy-guide/source).

This causes error 404 and deploy-guide post-gates to fail
(cherry picked from commit ccd542f7ea26d792ca8a07539f66fac6dfddbfb9)

Change-Id: I05e49bbcef564ad4f3d80f0649ccf191d9f8b59d

commit_message:
Don't install criu for arm64/s390x prior to artful

The criu package doesn't exist for arm64/s390x prior to artful,
causing an install hook failure. Let's not attempt to install
it when that is the case.

Change-Id: If0cc517d9e607604e427aab385fabd8a9a193fdf
Closes-Bug: #1748235

[{'created': '2018-04-07 09:41:44.000000000', 'message': "audittemplate list returns deleted Audit Templates

When we call audittemplate list without filters, it returns all Audit
Templates that are not deleted as expected. If we add any filter to
query and context.show_deleted is None (we request only current AT),
query.filter_by adds filter to joined table (for example, goals, results
 in query like JOIN goals ... WHERE ... goals.deleted_at IS NULL) not to
 model's table (AuditTemplate in our case).

We change call for filter_by to filter, explicitly point to model that
we want to filter.

Change-Id: I4d2f44fa149aee564c62a69822c6ad79de5bba8a
Closes-bug: 1761956
"}, {'created': '2018-04-10 11:12:26.000000000', 'message': "Added _get_model_list base method for all get_*_list methods

When we call audittemplate list without filters, it returns all Audit
Templates that are not deleted, as expected. If we add any filter to
query and context.show_deleted is None (we request only current AT),
query.filter_by adds filter to joined table (for example, goals, results
 in a query like JOIN goals ... WHERE ... goals.deleted_at IS NULL) not
to model's table (AuditTemplate in our case).

We change call for filter_by to filter, explicitly point to model that
we want to filter.

Also, we moved query generating code to new method _get_model_list(). As
a result we applied same fix to all of the other models.

Change-Id: I4d2f44fa149aee564c62a69822c6ad79de5bba8a
Closes-bug: 1761956
"}]
commit_message:
Added _get_model_list base method for all get_*_list methods

When we call audittemplate list without filters, it returns all Audit
Templates that are not deleted, as expected. If we add any filter to
query and context.show_deleted is None (we request only current AT),
query.filter_by adds filter to joined table (for example, goals, results
 in a query like JOIN goals ... WHERE ... goals.deleted_at IS NULL) not
to model's table (AuditTemplate in our case).

We change call for filter_by to filter, explicitly point to model that
we want to filter.

Also, we moved query generating code to new method _get_model_list(). As
a result we applied same fix to all of the other models.

Change-Id: I4d2f44fa149aee564c62a69822c6ad79de5bba8a
Closes-bug: 1761956

[{'created': '2017-06-22 10:06:45.000000000', 'message': 'Enable the HA deployment by default

With the HA NG work having landed, the impact of pacemaker
is reduced and only very few core services are being managed
by pacemaker. Since the HA deployments work just fine
with a single node, it makes little sense to use the non-ha
deployment as default any longer (Also because downstream
we do the default to the HA deployment by default and this
keeps confusing users)

The change in OOOQ-extras try to
change the way the pacemaker env files are used.

commit_message:
Enable the HA deployment by default

With the HA NG work having landed, the impact of pacemaker
is reduced and only very few core services are being managed
by pacemaker. Since the HA deployments work just fine
with a single node, it makes little sense to use the non-ha
deployment as default any longer (Also because downstream
we do the default to the HA deployment by default and this
keeps confusing users)

The change in OOOQ-extras try to
change the way the pacemaker env files are used.

Depends-On: I3a486d22b30ffdb6053b3d917dea373c1361df81
Change-Id: Ibfc86bc6e7f589a20fc82ad161d69e5c8c7a8cb8

commit_message:
IBM XIV: enable FC zoning to all the ports

Define FC host just considers connected FC target ports, which should
enable host to connect to all the storage FC ports for zoning.

Change-Id: Ibb20917c8ed80cb1413de1d61104d495605ec3df
Closes-Bug:#1759994

commit_message:
Add NetworkErrorException for socket.error

Sometimes rest_client can meet connection refused socket error
if the server is not listening on socket port yet. This patch
maps this error to NetworkErrorException so up layer caller can
handle it properly.

Change-Id: I946026221ded380b55d566ed9b1346e58386d167

commit_message:
Add volumes_links attribute in list_volumes schema

When GETting os-volumes, the returned list of volumes respects the
osapi_max_limit configuration parameter but does not provide a link to
the next element in the list. But volumes_links attribute not allowd in
volume list. We need to add volumes_links attribute in tempest.

Implements: blueprint resource-links-attribute-add
Change-Id: I8721b9648e22273232b108c67250749eda6c506a
Closes-Bug: 1504641

commit_message:
Add virtual_interfaces_links attribute in list_virtual_interfaces schema

When GETting os-virtual-interfaces, the returned list of
virtual_interfaces respects the osapi_max_limit configuration parameter
but does not provide a link to the next element in the list. But
virtual_interfaces_links attribute not allowd in virtual_interfaces
list. We need to add virtual_interfaces_links attribute in tempest.

Change-Id: If7fb9c4529a2413032decd29efb3c0433dd86a8a
Implements: blueprint resource-links-attribute-add
Related-Bug: 1504641

commit_message:
Gate fix: Cap hacking to avoid gate failure

hacking is not capped in g-r and it is in
blacklist for requirement as hacking new version
can break the gate jobs.

Hacking can break gate jobs because of various
reasons:
- There might be new rule addition in hacking
- Some rules becomes default from non-default
- Updates in pycodestyle etc

That was the main reason it was not added in g-r
auto sync also. Most of the project maintained the
compatible and cap the hacking version in
test-requirements.txt and update to new version when
project is ready. Bumping new version might need code
fix also on project side depends on what new in that
version.

If project does not have cap the hacking version then,
there is possibility of gate failure whenever new hacking
version is released by QA team.

Example of such failure in recent release of hacking 1.1.0
- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-May/130282.html

Change-Id: I05790c5f946a4127fe6c8d9867cc618cb83d67fb
